```ts
export type DeepReadonly<T> =
  T extends (...args: any[]) => any ? T
  : T extends readonly (infer U)[] ? readonly DeepReadonly<U>[]
  : T extends object ? { readonly [K in keyof T]: DeepReadonly<T[K]> }
  : T;
```

Functions are left alone (you don't want to `readonly`-mark call signatures). Arrays use `readonly U[]` so both `push` and index writes are disallowed. The object branch maps each key with `readonly` and recurses. Primitives fall through unchanged.

Fix this CQRS sketch so the read side does not share the write-side aggregate state type and reads go through a dedicated ReadStore.

