`fromCallback` wraps an imperative subscription as an actor. The callback receives `sendBack` (push events to the parent) and `receive` (subscribe to parent-sent events), and returns a cleanup function called on stop. Events pushed via `sendBack` appear in the parent's `on:` handlers like any other event.

