`assign(({ spawn }) => ...)` creates a child actor whose lifetime is tied to that context slot. Each tab's internal state (content, cursor, dirty flag) lives inside its own actor, so sibling tabs can't accidentally mutate each other's state. The parent holds only `ActorRefFrom<typeof tabLogic>` and addresses children via `sendTo`.

