A history pseudostate (`type: 'history'`) remembers the most recently active child of its parent. When an external transition targets the history node, the parent re-enters and the machine jumps back to whichever child was last active. `history: 'shallow'` (default) remembers the direct child; `'deep'` recursively restores descendants.

```typescript
